hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: GIT_REPO
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: URL of the Git repository, should be https not ssh.

com.cloudbees.plugins.credentials.Creden.name: TOKEN
com.cloudbees.plugins.credentials.Creden.description: Private access token for the Git repository

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: IMAGE_TAG
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Image tag of the operator to be installed

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: CHART_VERSION
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Version of operator chart to be installed

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: CHART_LOCATION
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Absolute path in the system where the operator charts are downloaded.

hudson.model.StringParameterValue.name: NAMESPACE
hudson.model.StringParameterValue.description: Namespace to install the operator chart

org.jenkinsci.plugins.pipeline.modeldefi.value: values_yaml="./values.yaml" if [ -f "$values_yaml" ]; then echo "values.yaml present: $values_yaml" else echo "Error: File does not exist: $values_yaml" exit 1 fi
license=$(yq '.licenseKey' values.yaml) if [[ "$license" == "null" || "$license" == "" ]]; then echo "Error: License key not found." exit 1 else echo "License check successful." fi

""" image_tag=\$(yq '.image.tag' values.yaml) if [[ "\$image_tag" == "${params.IMAGE_TAG}" ]]; then echo "Image tag check successful." else echo "Error: Incorrect image tag. Found \$image_tag, expecting ${params.IMAGE_TAG}." exit 1 fi """

""" status=\$(helm ls -n ${params.NAMESPACE} -o yaml | yq '(.[] | select(.name == "${params.RELEASE_NAME}") | .status)') version=\$(helm ls -n ${params.NAMESPACE} -o yaml | yq '(.[] | select(.name == "${params.RELEASE_NAME}") | .app_version)') echo "Chart status is: \$status." echo "Chart version is: \$version." if [ "\$status" != "deployed" ]; then exit 1 fi if [ "\$version" != "${params.CHART_VERSION}" ]; then exit 1 fi """
